Mexican Afores to Invest Up to 8% in Commodities

-- B y   B e n   B a i n
-- 
2011-12-07T20:21:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-07/mexican-afores-to-invest-up-to-8-in-commodities-correct-.html
(Corrects spelling of head of regulatory agency head and
clarifies rule contents in second paragraph.)  Mexican pension funds, known as
Afores, will be allowed to invest up to 8 percent in
commodities, said Pedro Ordorica, the head of the nation’s
pension fund regulator.  Rules on Afores’ corporate governance were published today
in the nation’s gazette, Ordorica told reporters at an event in
Mexico City.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ben Bain in New York at 
 bbain2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
